solutions.content:
Get minutes equivalent for hour hand on a scale of 0-60, in the code below hrm is used to denote that.
We know that at max, the difference can be 180 degrees, or 30 units in minute equivalent scale, we use this condition and calculate appropriately.
```
class Solution {
public:
    double angleClock(int hour, int minutes) {
        double hrm,mn;
        mn=minutes;
        hrm = hour%12*5;
        hrm+=mn/12.0;
        if(abs(mn-hrm)>30)
            return mn>hrm?(60-mn+hrm)*6:(60-hrm+mn)*6;
        else
            return abs(mn-hrm)*6;
    }
};
```

