solutions.content:
BFS solution is straigh forward.

1. Make a hashmap from number to list indices which will store a number mapped to list of indices where it is seen.
2. Do a BFS with visited array and every index we will do four case.
	1.  if currently polled index from queue is n-1 then we found answer.
	2.  add index+1 to bfs queue if its not visited.
	3. add index-1 to bfs queue if not visited.
	4. Iterate through the list which contains same number as arr[index] and add indices which are not visited.
with this we will get solution.

**NOTE:**
Main trick here is that as soon we iterate through the list of matches arr[index], I am clearing the list, because if indices in a list are already added once, we don't need to iterate through list because next time iterating through same list only results in not adding them to queue as they will already be visited. Since we are doing clear part inside for loop we don't need to use visited array we can just use (pos != index) if condition.


Time: O(N)
Space: O(N)




```
class Solution {
    public int minJumps(int[] arr) {
        int n = arr.length;

        Map<Integer, List<Integer>> finder = new HashMap<>();

        for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
            finder.computeIfAbsent(arr[i], v -> new ArrayList<Integer>());
            finder.get(arr[i]).add(i);
        }

        boolean[] visited = new boolean[n];

        Queue<Integer> current = new LinkedList<Integer>();

        current.add(0);
        visited[0] = true;

        int steps = 0;
        while (!current.isEmpty()) {
            int x = current.size();

            for (int i = 0; i < x; ++i) {
                int index = current.poll();
                if (index == n-1) {
                    return steps;
                }

                if ((index + 1) < n && !visited[index+1]) {
                    visited[index + 1] = true;
                    current.add(index + 1);
                }

                if (index - 1 >= 0 && !visited[index-1]) {
                    visited[index - 1] = true;
                    current.add(index - 1);
                }

                for (int pos : finder.get(arr[index])) {
                    if (pos != index) {
                        visited[pos] = true;
                        current.add(pos);
                    }
                }

                // Clearing the list so we won't stuck in forloop at step 39 every time. 
                finder.get(arr[index]).clear();
            }
            steps++;
        }
        return -1;
    }
}
```

