---

Background:

- Some JavaScript methods return `undefined`, some return `false`, and some `-1` on not found logic
- As you go down different solutions, you will have more javascript than problem solving itself :) (or may be not)
- Depending on if we have enough memory or not, we can choose one of the answers
  - I would choose 1st solution `Set`
  - Or, if someone says no more memory, then would choose the 4th solution, the simpler `for (i) for (j)` loop

By reading post this you might become good in JavaScript, if not problem solving, or both :)

---

**Algo:**

- Finding if we have an element that is double or half is the question
- That element should be not be same (which means element cannot be `0` because `0/2 = 0* 2 = 0`)
- For each element `e`, as we move to right of array:
  - Check if its `double` or `half` exists in our cache (say `Set/Map/Obj/Array/etc`)
    - If so, we found an `different` element ( `i != j` condition of question) so return `true`
  - Now that we have seen this `e`, put in in the cache

Hope it is simple to understand.

