solutions.content:
Check if there exists `i != j` so that `arr[i] = 2 * arr[j]`.

# Explanation

Store all the elements of `arr`  in a HashMap or HashSet and then check. 

Note the corner case of `[0]`.

The time complexity is O(n).

# C++ Solution

```cpp
class Solution {
public:
    bool checkIfExist(vector<int>& arr) {
        unordered_map<int, int> s;
        for (int x: arr)
            s[x]++;
        for (int x: arr)
            if (x != 0 && s.find(x * 2) != s.end())
                return true;
            else if (x == 0 && s[x] >= 2)
                return true;
        return false;
    }
};
```

