**Key points:**
* The title should have gave away the solution already.
* What can I say, it is a bit evil since it only covers 26 lower case English letters. But don't blame me, it is in the constraints.
* Just keep counting 26 letters. Increase by one side decrease by the other side. Like two letter histograms overlaping and canceling each other.
* At the end, add up either all positive or all negative counts, it will give the difference.
```
  int minSteps(const string & s, const string & t) {
    int ct[26] {};
