# Intuition
As it is an anagram, we just need to know if there are any characters that string s has but t does not.

# Approach
Keep a frequency tracker vector for the alphabets in string s and t. If the 3 a's are present in string s, increment the counter as many times. But if two a's are already present in string t, decrement the counter as we already have those. Now iterate through our frequency vector and see if there are alphabets that are present in s but not t, and add that value to final answer. 
It can happen that string t has 2 b's but string s doesnt, meaning freq1[1]=-2. What do we do in that case? We dont care about it, as the operation is substitution and new characters will be added to there place. Hence the method max(freq1[i], 0).

